explanation: The solution iterates through each character in `chars` to build a frequency map. Then, for each word in `words`, it checks if all characters can be formed from `chars` using the frequency map. If a word is valid, its length is added to the total count.  The time complexity is O(N*M) due to the nested loops, where N is the number of words and M is the maximum length of a word. The space complexity is O(M) due to the frequency maps.

